<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1734,1975]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1734,1759]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[283,404,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Both sexes</emphasis>
. Setae 
<emphasis box="[492,513,1735,1759]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">f2</emphasis>
present, prodorsal shield entire, prodorsal and hysteronotal shield with lacunae. 
<emphasis box="[151,209,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Male</emphasis>
. Adanal suckers toothed, adanal shields represented by 2 pairs of sclerites, adanal apodemes absent, epimerites I Y-shaped, terminal lamellae short tongue-shaped, aedeagus not extending beyond adanal suckers, hysterosoma with small metapodosomal sclerites. 
<emphasis box="[759,843,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Female</emphasis>
. Primary spermaduct short, without monotonous proximal enlargement toward spermatheca; head of spermatheca small conical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
